data.title: World Literature in Translations: Faiz Ahmed Faiz Semester 6 Session 2018-2022
data.meta_description: finaalll - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. This document provides a summary of works by the Pakistani poet Faiz Ahmed Faiz. It includes a biography of Faiz, summarizing his educational background and involvement in progressive literary movements in India. It also provides summaries of critical analyses of two of Faiz's poems: "Last Night" and "O! Restless Heart." For each poem, it discusses themes of love, revolution, and opposition to colonial British rule in India/Pakistan. The document is divided into sections written by three students analyzing different aspects of Faiz's works.
